<paragraph blockId="13.[173,1128,422,1187]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
Diagnosis – The new species resembles externally certain members of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[173,251,456,481]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Haderonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tancrei">
<emphasis box="[173,251,456,481]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">tancrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group but has more vivid bluish-grey colouration and complete pattern. It appears as on average much larger than the former species (wingspan 
<quantity box="[174,303,523,549]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.05" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="40.5" valueMax="42.0" valueMin="39.0">39–42 mm</quantity>
) and usually somewhat larger than the externally also similar 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Varga" baseAuthorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ctenoceratoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. argyrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, occurring with them sympatrically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[173,1128,422,1187]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Varga &amp; Gyulai &amp; Ronkay &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="2018" box="[234,529,590,616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ctenoceratoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyanochrea">
<emphasis box="[234,529,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Ctenoceratoda cyanochrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Varga" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[876,997,590,616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ctenoceratoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrea">
<emphasis box="[876,997,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. argyrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its less curved reniform stigma having relatively shorter acute whitish spot basally; stronger defined, ochreous orbicular stigma (it is obsolescent in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Varga" baseAuthorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ctenoceratoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. argyrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); longer, terminally acute claviform stigma; and the light ochreous, finely brownish defined (not whitish and diffuse) subterminal line.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[173,1128,422,1187]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
The new species differs from the related 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[730,840,758,784]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Haderonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tancrei">
<emphasis box="[730,840,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. tancrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[901,1021,758,784]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ctenoceratoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graeseri">
<emphasis box="[901,1021,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. graeseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1036,1118,758,785]" captionStart="Figs 9–16" captionStartId="10.[137,182,1359,1381]" captionTargetBox="[140,1087,208,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[137,1089,204,1330]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 9–16. Ctenoceratoda spp. 9–12 = C. scotosparsa, sp. n., Mongolia, Govi Altay aimak: 9–10 = paratype, male, 11–12 = paratype, female; 13–15 = C. cyanochrea sp. n., Mongolia, Khovd aimak: 13 = holotype, male, 14 = paratype, male, 15 = paratype, female; 16 = C. grae-" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5734640/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) by its smaller size and the bluish shaded grey ground colour while the larger relatives usually have ochreous-brownish forewings without any bluish hue.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[173,1128,422,1187]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
In male genitalia, the most conspicuous character is the relatively large, not inflated rounded triangular “head” of the cucullus (
<figureCitation box="[880,1018,892,918]" captionStart="Figs 47–52" captionStartId="19.[174,219,1526,1548]" captionTargetBox="[179,1117,209,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-21@19.[179,1121,189,1498]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 47–52. Ctenoceratoda spp. male genitalia. 47–48 = C. cyanochrea sp. n., paratype, Mongolia, slide No.: RL8644; 49–50 = C. mallopyga mallopyga sp. n., paratype, Pakistan, slide No.: VZ9238; 51–52 = C. contempta (Püngeler, 1914), Semiretshye, slide No.: RL11754" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734654" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5734654/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Figs 47, 48</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus and vesica is much larger than in the former species. Brush organ is well developed, opposed to the externally similar species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alpheraky" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[896,1034,959,986]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ctenoceratoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khorgossi">
<emphasis box="[896,1034,959,986]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. khorgossi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, e.g. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Varga &amp; Gyulai &amp; Ronkay &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="2018" box="[225,388,993,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ctenoceratoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scotosparsa">
<emphasis box="[225,388,993,1019]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. scotosparsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Varga" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[453,572,993,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ctenoceratoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrea">
<emphasis box="[453,572,993,1019]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. argyrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on this character, this species cannot be mixed with either species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="1974" box="[604,760,1027,1053]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Haderonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sukharevae">
<emphasis box="[604,760,1027,1053]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. sukharevae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group since latter never have any brush organ.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[173,1128,422,1187]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
Distribution and bionomics. The 
<typeStatus box="[647,702,1094,1120]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
series of the new species was collected at lower altitudes of the Mongolian 
<collectingRegion box="[715,776,1127,1153]" country="Russia" name="Altay" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Altai</collectingRegion>
Mts. Its flight period is the mid-summer.
</paragraph>
